<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She's the glamorous Sunrise presenter with a passion for all things equestrian. </p>

<p>So it was no wonder Samantha Armytage looked thrilled to attend the prestigious Everest Carnival launch event in Sydney on Monday. </p>

<p>The 44-year-old looked glamorous as she posed next to a cream-coloured steed and she showed off her sexy bedhead hairstyle. </p>

<p>Looking good! Glamorous Samantha Armytage revealed her sexy bedhead hairstyle as she posed with a horse at the Everest Carnival launch in Sydney on Monday</p>

<p>Samantha was dressed to impress in a knee-length black frock with puffed sleeves and a high neckline. </p>

<p>She completed her timeless ensemble with a pair of elegant pointy-toed black heels and a brown leather headband. </p>

<p>For makeup, Samantha enhanced her famous features with copper eye shadow, faux lashes, rose blush, bubblegum pink lipstick and dramatic faux lashes. </p>

<p>Horsing around! The 44-year-old looked glamorous as she posed next to a cream-coloured steed</p>

<p>Also visible on her wedding finger was her diamond engagement ring from fiancé Richard Lavender. </p>

<p>Samantha, who grew up living on a sheep station in the Snowy Mountains of New South Wales, has long had an affinity to horses.</p>

<p>In 2017, the blonde even admitted that she uses horse shampoo to wash her hair. </p>

<p>Glamorous: Samantha (pictured presenting to media at the event) was dressed to impress in a knee-length black frock with puffed sleeves and a high neckline</p>

<p>During an episode of Sunrise, the presenter confessed that she keeps her mane shiny by washing her hair with Mane And Tail - a shampoo originally formulated for horses. </p>

<p>'I use horse shampoo...it's very good for you,' she admitted, leaving co-hosts David Koch and Natalie Barr stunned.  </p>

<p>'I bought it in America... 'Mane N Tail' shampoo. See how it shines?' she boasted as she ran her fingers through her ponytail. </p>

<p>Primped: For makeup, Samantha enhanced her famous features with copper eye shadow, faux lashes, rose blush, bubblegum pink lipstick and dramatic faux lashes</p>

<p>'See how I look like a thoroughbred and not a draft horse?' she jokingly added. </p>

<p>Samantha's colleagues seemed surprise at her choice of shampoo, but she remained adamant about its benefits.</p>

<p>'It’s very good for your hair...horse shampoo,' she proclaimed, 'You can wash the horse... then you can wash yourself, save money.'</p>

<p>The shampoo is already popular in the US and UK with highstreet shops like Urban Outfitters and Boots stocking it for human use.  </p>

